---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Accessibility Statement - Headen Tech Solutions"
  description="Accessibility statement for Headen Tech Solutions website. Our commitment to digital accessibility and WCAG 2.1 AA compliance."
>
  <Header />
  
  <main id="main-content">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-800 to-primary-900 text-white py-16">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Accessibility Statement</h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-primary-100 max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
            Our commitment to digital accessibility and inclusive design for all users.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Accessibility Content -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-card border border-neutral-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Our Commitment</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              Headen Tech Solutions is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. 
              We continually improve the user experience for everyone and apply the relevant accessibility standards.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Conformance Status</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
              This website strives to conform to WCAG 2.1 AA standards. We have implemented the following 
              accessibility features:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Semantic HTML structure with proper heading hierarchy</li>
              <li>Alternative text for images and visual content</li>
              <li>Keyboard navigation support throughout the site</li>
              <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum)</li>
              <li>Focus indicators for interactive elements</li>
              <li>Skip-to-content links for screen readers</li>
              <li>Form labels and error messaging</li>
              <li>Responsive design for various screen sizes</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Keyboard Navigation</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
              This website can be navigated using only a keyboard. Use the following keys:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Tab:</strong> Move forward through interactive elements</li>
              <li><strong>Shift + Tab:</strong> Move backward through interactive elements</li>
              <li><strong>Enter:</strong> Activate links and buttons</li>
              <li><strong>Space:</strong> Activate buttons and checkboxes</li>
              <li><strong>Arrow Keys:</strong> Navigate within menus and lists</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Screen Reader Support</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              This website is designed to work with screen readers and other assistive technologies. 
              We use semantic HTML, proper ARIA labels, and descriptive text to ensure content is 
              accessible to users with visual impairments.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Color and Contrast</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              We maintain sufficient color contrast ratios throughout the website. Text and background 
              combinations meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards with a minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for 
              normal text and 3:1 for large text.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Forms and Interactive Elements</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
              All forms include proper labels and error messaging. Interactive elements have:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Clear, descriptive labels</li>
              <li>Error messages that identify the problem</li>
              <li>Instructions for completing forms</li>
              <li>Visible focus indicators</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Known Limitations</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              While we strive to make this website fully accessible, we acknowledge that there may 
              be areas for improvement. We are continuously working to enhance accessibility and 
              welcome feedback from users.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Feedback and Accommodations</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
              If you encounter accessibility barriers or need accommodations, please contact us. 
              We are committed to providing alternative formats and assistance as needed.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
              <p class="text-neutral-700">
                <strong>Email:</strong> 
                <a href="mailto:consulting@headentechsolutions.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-800 underline">
                  consulting@headentechsolutions.com
                </a>
              </p>
              <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-2">
                <strong>Response Time:</strong> We typically respond within 24 hours
              </p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Testing and Evaluation</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              We regularly test this website using automated accessibility tools and manual 
              testing methods. Our testing includes:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
              <li>Automated accessibility scanning tools</li>
              <li>Keyboard-only navigation testing</li>
              <li>Screen reader compatibility testing</li>
              <li>Color contrast verification</li>
              <li>User testing with people with disabilities</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Ongoing Improvements</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
              We are committed to continuous improvement of our website's accessibility. 
              This includes regular updates, user feedback integration, and staying current 
              with accessibility best practices and standards.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-primary-100 border border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-4 mt-8">
              <p class="text-primary-800 text-sm">
                <strong>Last Updated:</strong> December 2024
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
